    "headline": "Unknown 2024-10-05 price-manipulation incident",
    "what_happened": "On October 5, 2024, a price manipulation attack targeted the AIZPT Token on BSC, resulting in an estimated loss of approximately 34 BNB. The attacker exploited a price oracle vulnerability to drain funds from the protocol's liquidity pools.",
    "why_it_matters": "This incident highlights the critical importance of robust price oracle implementations and resistance to manipulation. Protocols should use TWAP (Time-Weighted Average Price) oracles, multiple data sources, and implement price deviation thresholds to prevent similar attacks. The availability of a public PoC also underscores the need for thorough security audits before deployment.",
