  "exploit_path": {
    "summary": "The attacker (0x8408497c18882bfb61be9204cfff530f4ee18320) executed a price manipulation attack against the AIZPT Token protocol on BSC. The attack transaction (0x5e694707337cca979d18f9e45f40e81d6ca341ed342f1377f563e779a746460d) leveraged vulnerabilities in the token's pricing mechanism to extract value from liquidity pools. Evidence from the DeFiHackLabs proof-of-concept (AIZPTToken_exp.sol) indicates the attacker interacted with multiple contracts including the AIZPT token contract, WBNB (0xbb4CdB9CBd36B01bD1cBaEBF2De08d9173bc095c), and USDT (0x55d398326f99059fF775485246999027B3197955), suggesting a cross-pool manipulation strategy. The attacker successfully extracted approximately 34 BNB before the exploit was identified.",
